  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Social Accountability Gh IMANI</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Two key aspects are involved in this one year application. One is focused on exploring accountability in the Ghana cocoa board herein referred to as COCOBOD, by exploring revenue management within the institution to improve transparency around the operations of COCOBOD. This will enhance the derivation of maximum value from its activities to support growth and development of the cocoa sector. Activities to achieve the aim of project include operational research on revenue management and advocacy. The second project is to promote social accountability in domestic revenue mobilization and service delivery in 15 municipalities in Ghana. This project aims at improving and strengthening the voice of citizens to demand accountability and transparency in the spending of internally generated funds. Activities will include undertaking an operational research for evidence and using same to advocate for efficiency in spending of local authorities. These two projects are countervailing measures to the embassy&apos;s support to the cocoa sector and that of enhancing tax revenue mobilization in municipalities in Ghana.</narrative>
  </description>
